Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.39,0:21:42.53,Default,what is the name of this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.53,0:21:45.98,Default,Drop it view controller,\Nthat's ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.74,0:21:49.36,Default,Weak self equals self.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.46,0:21:52.69,Default,So now I've created a\Nweak pointer to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.05,0:21:54.30,Default,and now I can use that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.48,0:21:55.23,Default,Weak self.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.13,0:21:57.63,Default,Okay? Also down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.02,0:22:00.40,Default,Weak self.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.57,0:22:04.43,Default,Alright? So if I ever got\Ndropped out of the heap,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.76,0:22:06.66,Default,and no one had a\Nstrong pointer to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.84,0:22:09.01,Default,these weak self pointers\Nwould all go to nil,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.01,0:22:11.06,Default,but that would be fine,\Nbecause if I'm not around,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.06,0:22:13.45,Default,then this action doesn't\Nmean anything anyway, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.45,0:22:14.29,Default,I'm the controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.99,0:22:17.73,Default,So, so it's all perfectly\Nfine to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.94,0:22:21.05,Default,Okay? Any questions\Nabout what we did there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.05,0:22:23.34,Default,Because that's an important\Nthing to understand, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.91,0:22:29.91,Default,Alright. One last thing we have\Nto do is when the gesture ends,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.29,0:22:33.23,Default,the pan gesture ends, and\Nwe remove the animator,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.50,0:22:36.14,Default,we're going to want to say\Nself dot game view dot path
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.14,0:22:36.82,Default,equals nil.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.60,0:22:43.07,Default,Okay? Because this action, once\Nthis thing is removed from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.38,0:22:45.16,Default,this action is not going\Nto execute anymore,
